  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2020-06-22",
    "date": "2020-07-29T15:46:29Z",
    "text": "This bill calls for states and electric or natural gas utilities to place a moratorium on utility disconnections during the emergency relating to the COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) outbreak. In addition, the bill calls for states and utilities to ensure that\n\n reasonable efforts are made to safely reconnect electric and natural gas consumers that have lost service; fees for reconnection services, late fees, and other penalties are waived; and there are no increases in cost-of-service to consumers."
  },
